      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> </strong>any <strong>roughly chopped aubergine </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock</strong>,<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and<strong> drained cannellini beans</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened slightly</p>",
